<body><div type="diplomatic"><pb facs="#facs_452" id="225r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee"><del rend="crossout"><ab facs="#facs_452_r1l22">Thomas von Roſemberg </ab>
</del></div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content"><del rend="crossout"><ab facs="#facs_452_r1l23"><expan>Vnſ<ex>er</ex></expan> dıenſt Thomas von <expan>Roſemb<ex>er</ex>g</expan> als Jr vns <expan>verſchr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt / </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_452_r1l24">wıe Jr in <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>m</expan> brıef niht <expan>v<ex>er</ex>ſteen</expan> könnet / ob Jr vnd dıe <expan>eẅ<ex>r</ex>n</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_452_r1l25">vnd das eẅr vor vns vnd den <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> ſıcher ſeyt etc / das haben </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_452_r1l27">wır wol <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan> . Nu haben wır eẅch 
<del rend="strikethrough">nehſt </del>
<add><ab facs="#facs_452_r1l26">ın <expan>demſ<ex>elben</ex></expan> <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>m</expan> nehſten <expan>br<ex>ief</ex></expan> </ab></add> <expan>geantw<ex>ur</ex>t</expan> / des Jr </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_452_r1l28">pılleıch ein genügen gehabt hett als wır meynen . Wıe <expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan> </ab>
</del><pb facs="#facs_455"/><del rend="crossout"><ab facs="#facs_455_r1l1">ſo ſüllt Jr von der geſchıcht <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> dıe eẅr <expan>brud<ex>er</ex></expan> hanns von <expan>Roſemb<ex>er</ex>g</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_455_r1l2">an vns vnd den <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> getan hat . vor vns vnd den <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> ſıcher ſeyn </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_455_r1l4">Als Jr denn 
        <add><ab facs="#facs_455_r1l3">von vns </ab></add> begert ʒu wıſſen von der <expan>eẅ<ex>r</ex>n</expan> vnd des <expan>eẅ<ex>r</ex>n</expan> <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> / vvenn </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_455_r1l5">Jr vns benennt . wer dıe <expan>eẅ<ex>r</ex>n</expan> . vnd was das eẅr ſey . ſo <expan>welle<ex>n</ex></expan> wır </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_455_r1l6">eẅch darcʒu auch <expan>antw<ex>ur</ex>t<ex>en</ex></expan> </ab>
</del>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_452" id="225r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab><del rend="crossout">Thomas von Rosemberg</del></ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><del rend="crossout"><expan>Uns<ex>er</ex></expan> dienst. Thomas von
                                    <expan>Rosemb<ex>er</ex>g</expan>, als ir uns
                                    <expan>verschr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt, wie ir in
                                    <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>m</expan> brief niht
                                <expan>v<ex>er</ex>steen</expan> könnet, ob ir und die
                                    <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan> und das ewr vor uns und den
                                    <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan> sicher seyt etc., das haben wir
                            wol <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan>. Nu haben wir ewch <add>in
                                        <expan>dems<ex>elben</ex></expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex>m</expan> nehsten
                                <expan>br<ex>ief</ex></expan></add>
<expan>geantw<ex>ur</ex>t</expan>, des ir pilleich ein genügen gehabt
                        hett, als wir meynen. Wie <expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan></del>
<pb facs="#facs_455"/><del rend="crossout">So süllt ir von der geschicht
                            <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> die ewr <expan>brud<ex>er</ex></expan>
                            Hanns von <expan>Rosemb<ex>er</ex>g</expan> an uns und den
                            <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan> getan hat, vor uns und den
                            <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan> sicher seyn, als ir denn <add>von
                                uns</add> begert zu wissen von der <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan> und
                            des <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan>
<expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan>, wenn ir uns benennt, wer die
                            <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan> und was das ewr sey, so
                            <expan>welle<ex>n</ex></expan> wir ewch darczu auch
                            <expan>antw<ex>ur</ex>t<ex>en</ex></expan>.</del></ab>
</div>
</div></body>
